---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="我的符號：一份個人宣言"
  description="從一個污點出發，疊建出十二層符號——這不是 LOGO 設計，這是我對「何謂能力」的哲學宣言。中英雙語。"
  lang="zh"
>
  <article class="manifesto">
    <a href="/writing" class="back-link">← Writing</a>

    <header class="manifesto-header">
      <div class="post-meta">
        <time>Jun 25, 2026</time>
        <span class="lang-badge">中 / EN</span>
        <span class="tag">個人哲學</span>
        <span class="tag">Personal Brand</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="manifesto-title">
        <span class="lang-zh">我的符號</span><span class="lang-en">My Symbol</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="manifesto-subtitle lang-zh">一份個人宣言</p>
      <p class="manifesto-subtitle lang-en"><em>A Personal Declaration</em></p>
    </header>

    <div class="symbol-hero">
      <img src="/images/symbolic-reminder/Competence.svg" alt="Competence — the complete symbol" class="symbol-img symbol-hero-img" />
    </div>

    <section class="declaration-opening">
      <p class="lang-zh">幾千個小時的演講、幾本書的邊際筆記之後，我開始理解一件事：一個人的能力，不是從優點開始建構的，而是從你願不願意正視自己的污點開始的。這個符號系統，是我試圖把那個理解，畫出來。</p>
      <p class="lang-en"><em>After thousands of hours of lectures and annotated books, I came to understand one thing: competence is not built from strengths — it is built from whether you are willing to face your own stain. This symbol system is my attempt to draw that understanding.</em></p>

      <p class="lang-zh">Jordan B. Peterson 的研究橫跨宗教、心理學與認知科學。從他的演講，我進入了榮格的陰影理論，以及約瑟夫·坎伯的英雄之旅。每一條線索，都讓我更清楚：真正的能力，不是避開困難，而是走過它。</p>
      <p class="lang-en"><em>Jordan B. Peterson's work spans religion, psychology, and cognitive science. Through his lectures, I found my way to Jung's concept of the Shadow, and to Joseph Campbell's Hero's Journey. Each thread made it clearer: true competence is not about avoiding difficulty — it is about walking through it.</em></p>

      <p class="lang-zh">每個符號，從前一個幾何形狀延伸而來。這本身就是宣言：能力不是空降的，是一層一層疊建的。</p>
      <p class="lang-en"><em>Each symbol grows from the geometry of the one before it. That itself is the declaration: competence does not arrive from outside — it is built, layer by layer, from within.</em></p>
    </section>

    <hr class="section-divider" />

    <section class="symbol-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">
        <span class="lang-zh">I. 起點</span><span class="lang-en">I. The Beginning</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="symbol-block">
        <div class="symbol-label">Core · Stain · Truth</div>
        <div class="symbol-content">
          <div class="symbol-text">
            <p class="lang-zh">這是一切的起點——也是最難承認的那個。榮格稱之為 Shadow：我們每個人身上都有一個不願正視的核心，一個弱點、一個恐懼、一個無法接受的自我面向。</p>
            <p class="lang-en"><em>This is where everything begins — and the hardest part to admit. Jung called it the Shadow: the aspect of ourselves we refuse to see. A weakness. A fear. A part of the self we cannot accept.</em></p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/symbolic-reminder/Core_Stain_Truth.svg" alt="Core, Stain, Truth" class="symbol-img symbol-small" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="symbol-block">
        <div class="symbol-label">Circle of Arms · Embrace</div>
        <div class="symbol-content">
          <div class="symbol-text">
            <p class="lang-zh">下一步，不是消除它，而是擁抱它。將雙臂圍繞那個污點——不是為了隱藏它，而是為了宣告：「它是我的。我不逃了。」</p>
            <p class="lang-en"><em>The next step is not to eliminate it, but to embrace it. Wrap your arms around the stain — not to hide it, but to declare: "This is mine. I am done running."</em></p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/symbolic-reminder/Circle_of_Arms.svg" alt="Circle of Arms" class="symbol-img symbol-medium" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="section-divider" />

    <section class="symbol-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">
        <span class="lang-zh">II. 視野</span><span class="lang-en">II. Vision</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="symbol-block">
        <div class="symbol-label">Vision · Embrace Weakness</div>
        <div class="symbol-content">
          <div class="symbol-text">
            <p class="lang-zh">兩個圓圈，代表一個更完整的視野——看見自己的全部，包含那些你不喜歡的部分。能看見弱點，才能超越弱點。</p>
            <p class="lang-en"><em>Two circles represent a more complete vision — seeing all of yourself, including the parts you dislike. You can only transcend your weakness if you can first see it.</em></p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/symbolic-reminder/Vision_embrace_weakness.svg" alt="Vision, Embrace Weakness" class="symbol-img symbol-medium" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="symbol-block">
        <div class="symbol-label">Awareness · Intelligence</div>
        <div class="symbol-content">
          <div class="symbol-text">
            <p class="lang-zh">加入了一條垂直線——你與時間的軸線。能看見過去的自己從哪裡來，看清楚現在在哪裡，並且想像未來可以去哪裡。這是意識的本質：不只是感覺，而是理解。</p>
            <p class="lang-en"><em>A vertical line is added — your axis with time. Seeing where you came from, understanding where you are, and imagining where you can go. This is the nature of intelligence: not just feeling, but understanding.</em></p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/symbolic-reminder/Awareness_Intelligence.svg" alt="Awareness, Intelligence" class="symbol-img symbol-medium" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="symbol-block">
        <div class="symbol-label">Growth · Hero's Journey</div>
        <div class="symbol-content">
          <div class="symbol-text">
            <p class="lang-zh">加入了橫線。坎伯的英雄之旅說：真正的成長，發生在你離開舒適圈、走向未知之後。這條橫線，是那條門檻——你選擇跨越，還是留在原地。</p>
            <p class="lang-en"><em>A horizontal line is added. Campbell's Hero's Journey says: true growth happens after you leave the comfort zone and step into the unknown. This horizontal line is that threshold — you choose to cross it, or you don't.</em></p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/symbolic-reminder/Growth_heros_journey.svg" alt="Growth, Hero's Journey" class="symbol-img symbol-medium" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="section-divider" />

    <section class="symbol-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">
        <span class="lang-zh">III. 意志與力量</span><span class="lang-en">III. Will &amp; Power</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="symbol-block">
        <div class="symbol-label">Will · Choice · Aim</div>
        <div class="symbol-content">
          <div class="symbol-text">
            <p class="lang-zh">十字準心。你站在原點，向四個方向都看得見，然後你選擇一個方向。這是意志的時刻：不是被動接受，而是主動選擇。</p>
            <p class="lang-en"><em>A crosshair. You stand at the center, seeing in all four directions, then you choose one. This is the moment of will: not passive acceptance, but active choice.</em></p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/symbolic-reminder/Will_Choice_Aim.svg" alt="Will, Choice, Aim" class="symbol-img symbol-medium" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="symbol-block">
        <div class="symbol-label">Power · Sword</div>
        <div class="symbol-content">
          <div class="symbol-text">
            <p class="lang-zh">符號的形狀改變了，它變成了一把劍。力量，不是來自外在的強大，而是來自你選擇了方向，並且願意承擔後果。</p>
            <p class="lang-en"><em>The shape transforms — it becomes a sword. Power is not an external strength. It comes from having chosen a direction, and being willing to bear the consequences.</em></p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/symbolic-reminder/Power_Sword.svg" alt="Power, Sword" class="symbol-img symbol-wide" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="symbol-block">
        <div class="symbol-label">Control · Sheath</div>
        <div class="symbol-content">
          <div class="symbol-text">
            <p class="lang-zh">劍要放入鞘中。真正的力量，不是一直揮劍，而是知道什麼時候不揮。控制力，是力量的升級，不是削弱。</p>
            <p class="lang-en"><em>The sword goes into the sheath. True power is not constant wielding — it is knowing when not to. Restraint is the upgrade to power, not its negation.</em></p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/symbolic-reminder/Control_Sheath.svg" alt="Control, Sheath" class="symbol-img symbol-wide" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="section-divider" />

    <section class="symbol-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">
        <span class="lang-zh">IV. 言語與公義</span><span class="lang-en">IV. Voice &amp; Justice</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="symbol-block">
        <div class="symbol-label">Mouth · Speech</div>
        <div class="symbol-content">
          <div class="symbol-text">
            <p class="lang-zh">現在你可以開口說話了。不是因為你已經完美，而是因為你已經正視了污點、擁抱了弱點、選擇了方向、掌握了力量。說話，是承擔。</p>
            <p class="lang-en"><em>Now you can speak. Not because you are perfect, but because you have faced your stain, embraced your weakness, chosen a direction, and mastered your power. To speak is to take responsibility.</em></p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/symbolic-reminder/Mouth_speech.svg" alt="Mouth, Speech" class="symbol-img symbol-wide" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="symbol-block">
        <div class="symbol-label">Justice · Balanced Scale · Libra</div>
        <div class="symbol-content">
          <div class="symbol-text">
            <p class="lang-zh">你說出的話，要與你的行動一致。你對自己設的標準，要與你對他人的標準一致。這是公義的本質：不偏不倚，一視同仁。</p>
            <p class="lang-en"><em>What you say must align with what you do. The standard you hold for yourself must match the standard you hold for others. This is the nature of justice: impartial and consistent.</em></p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/symbolic-reminder/Justice_Balanced_Scale_Libra.svg" alt="Justice, Balanced Scale, Libra" class="symbol-img symbol-wide" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="symbol-block">
        <div class="symbol-label">Meek Virtue · Control the Power</div>
        <div class="symbol-content">
          <div class="symbol-text">
            <p class="lang-zh">Meek，在古英文中不是「懦弱」，而是「力量在控制之下」。一個能控制自己力量的人，才真正擁有力量。</p>
            <p class="lang-en"><em>Meek, in its ancient meaning, does not mean weak — it means power under control. Only one who can control their power truly possesses it.</em></p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/symbolic-reminder/Meek_Virtue_control_the_power.svg" alt="Meek Virtue, Control the Power" class="symbol-img symbol-wide" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="section-divider" />

    <section class="symbol-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">
        <span class="lang-zh">V. 智慧之眼</span><span class="lang-en">V. The Wisdom Eye</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="symbol-block">
        <div class="symbol-label">Wisdom Eye · Own the Vision</div>
        <div class="symbol-content">
          <div class="symbol-text">
            <p class="lang-zh">它看得見整個符號——所有層次、所有路徑、所有可能性。擁有視野，不是說你能預見一切，而是說你願意看見真實。</p>
            <p class="lang-en"><em>It sees the entire symbol — all the layers, all the paths, all the possibilities. To own the vision is not to predict everything, but to be willing to see what is true.</em></p>
          </div>
          <img src="/images/symbolic-reminder/Wisdom_eye_Own_the_vision.svg" alt="Wisdom Eye, Own the Vision" class="symbol-img symbol-wide" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="section-divider" />

    <section class="declaration-closing">
      <div class="symbol-label competence-label">Competence</div>
      <div class="symbol-hero">
        <img src="/images/symbolic-reminder/Competence.svg" alt="Competence — the complete symbol" class="symbol-img symbol-hero-img" />
      </div>

      <p class="declaration-final lang-zh">這就是能力。</p>
      <p class="declaration-final lang-en"><em>This is Competence.</em></p>

      <p class="lang-zh">不是技術，不是學歷，不是表現——是一個人能夠正視自己的污點、擁抱弱點、選擇方向、控制力量、承擔說話、追求公義、謙遜有力，然後用智慧的眼睛看見全局的能力。</p>
      <p class="lang-en"><em>Not technique, not credentials, not performance — but the capacity of a person to face their own stain, embrace their weakness, choose a direction, control their power, speak with responsibility, pursue justice, hold strength with humility, and see the whole picture with a wise eye.</em></p>

      <p class="final-coda lang-zh">這個符號是我的起點，也是我的全部。每次我看見它，它都在提醒我：你準備好了。</p>
      <p class="final-coda lang-en"><em>This symbol is where I begin. And where I hold everything I am. Every time I see it, it reminds me: you are ready.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .manifesto {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--spacing-lg) var(--spacing-sm) var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

  .manifesto-header { margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg); }
  .post-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
  .lang-badge {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 0.1rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
  }
  .tag {
    background: var(--color-tag-bg);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    padding: 0.1rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
  }
  .manifesto-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 2.4rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .manifesto-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0.2rem 0 0;
  }

  /* override global lang-en display:inline → block for block elements */
  [data-lang="en"] p.lang-en { display: block; }
  [data-lang="en"] .manifesto-subtitle.lang-en { display: block; }

  .symbol-hero {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    margin: var(--spacing-lg) 0;
  }
  .symbol-hero-img {
    max-width: 300px;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .declaration-opening { margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg); }
  .declaration-opening p {
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .declaration-opening p.lang-zh { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--color-text); }
  .declaration-opening p.lang-en { font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); }

  .section-divider {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin: var(--spacing-lg) 0;
  }

  .symbol-section { margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm); }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 var(--spacing-md);
  }

  .symbol-block { margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg); }

  .symbol-label {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  /* image floated right, text on the left */
  .symbol-content {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .symbol-text { flex: 1; min-width: 0; }

  .symbol-img {
    display: block;
    height: auto;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .symbol-small  { width: 72px; }
  .symbol-medium { width: 96px; }
  .symbol-wide   { width: 130px; }

  [data-theme="dark"] .symbol-img { filter: invert(1); }

  .symbol-block p.lang-zh {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .symbol-block p.lang-en {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .declaration-closing { padding-top: var(--spacing-sm); }
  .competence-label {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .declaration-final {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: var(--spacing-md) 0 0.3rem;
  }
  .declaration-closing p.lang-zh {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .declaration-closing p.lang-en {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 var(--spacing-md);
  }
  .final-coda { font-weight: 500; }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .symbol-content { gap: 0.75rem; }
    .symbol-small  { width: 56px; }
    .symbol-medium { width: 72px; }
    .symbol-wide   { width: 100px; }
    .symbol-hero-img { max-width: 220px; }
  }
</style>
